title: Subdelegaciones (Mexico, 1788-1821)
name: Subdelegaciones (Mexico, 1788-1821)
description:
Subdelegaciones, local administrative units created by the Royal Ordinance of 1786.

These are the approximate boundaries of subdelegaciones created in 1786, but not implemented until 1788. They may serve as a basis to reconstruct the boundaries of alcald√≠as mayores. This work is based on scanned versions of Gerhard's district maps of New Spain and the northern frontier (I have no short-term plans to incorporate Gerhard's southern frontier). The drawings are imprecise and they did not necessarily register well with higher quality geographic information (present-day boundaries, rivers, elevation models). To solve contradictions I followed textual descriptions (e.g. rivers that serve as boundaries) and attempted to keep the most important towns and villages within the boundaries of the polygon.

I ask users who make changes to the files or find errors to let me know so I can improve this dataset in future versions. 

Please cite if used using the citation URL.
